      "node_id": "C_kwDOABII59oAKGJjMzBlOTUxNjMyNGQ4MmJkODU0MGE4MjU0NDA4NTU1M2E1OGFhYmM",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/bc30e9516324d82bd8540a82544085553a58aabc",
      "actor": null,
      "commit_id": null,
      "commit_url": null,
      "created_at": null,
      "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/bc30e9516324d82bd8540a82544085553a58aabc",
      "tree": {
        "sha": "b8ee131a243fbcb3d4af80b5e724c0df2b2111d6",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/b8ee131a243fbcb3d4af80b5e724c0df2b2111d6"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree b8ee131a243fbcb3d4af80b5e724c0df2b2111d6\nparent 5f33da9aa30ff80876f2f450b4370c446555bd71\nauthor Pol Espinasa <pol.espinasa@uab.cat> 1781164785 +0200\ncommitter Pol Espinasa <pol.espinasa@uab.cat> 1781173615 +0200\n\nwallet: move fAbortRescan reset into WalletRescanReserver reserve()\n\nReserving the wallet rescan is the first thing done when starting a rescan.\nAs part of the reservation, clear any leftover state from previous\nrescans (reset fAbortRescan). This prevents a race condition\nwhere an abort request arrives before the rescan loop starts; without\nthis reset, the abort could be ignored and the rescan would proceed.\n\nCo-authored-by: w0xlt <woltx@protonmail.com>\n",
